Telegram only offers true end-to-end encryption (E2E) in its “Secret Chats.” Regular chats are encrypted between your device and Telegram’s servers, meaning Telegram could access those messages. Secret Chats, however, encrypt messages so only the sender and receiver can read them—no one else, not even Telegram. This matters for privacy and security, as only E2E can fully protect messages from being seen by outsiders. To learn more, search for “Telegram Secret Chats,” “end-to-end encryption,” and “messenger security.”